Biofilm-forming capacity was assessed using the maximum cell index recorded from xCELLigence. Biofilm formation was assessed over a 12-hour period using xCELLigence-derived cell index values. 
A total of 36 biofilm samples were included in the analysis. The mean maximum biofilm index was 0.189 (SD = 0.081; median = 0.179).
Biofilm formation over time was first visualised using observed growth curves. A marked increase in biofilm formation was observed between approximately 4 and 7 hours.
Area under the curve was used as a summary measure of total biofilm burden over time. This measure captures both the magnitude and duration of biofilm formation during the 12-hour observation period.
